1
00:01:51,878 --> 00:01:55,678
Good afternoon and welcome to the
Phase II Press Conference of the

2
00:01:55,882 --> 00:01:59,045
upcoming mission for the
Global Precipitation Measurement.

3
00:02:00,353 --> 00:02:03,186
To discuss the mission we have
with us John Stockton

4
00:02:03,857 --> 00:02:07,850
GPM Project Formulation Manager
from NASA HQ.

5
00:02:08,895 --> 00:02:10,123
Mohan Bhargava...

6
00:02:10,597 --> 00:02:13,828
Project Manager and Spacecraft
Mission Director from GODDARD.

7
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:16,495
Over to you John.
- Thank you George.

8
00:02:17,403 --> 00:02:20,770
The Office of Management and Budget
released the President's 2004

9
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:25,604
fiscal year budget plan in early February
flagging off the GPM Launch.

10
00:02:26,412 --> 00:02:30,109
We have in the Formulation phase
of GPM taken steps to reduce risks

11
00:02:30,783 --> 00:02:33,445
to ensure a mission
confirmation review.

12
00:02:34,287 --> 00:02:38,018
That's where Mohan Bhargava,
our Project Manager comes in.

13
00:02:39,259 --> 00:02:41,853
Thank you John.
Good afternoon everybody.

14
00:02:42,729 --> 00:02:46,859
Before I come to Phase II, a quick update
on the recently concluded Phase I.

15
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:50,800
In Phase I we focused on the
Definition of Mission Scope,

16
00:02:51,137 --> 00:02:54,106
Systematic Measurement Approach
and Technology Roadmaps.

17
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:57,203
Will you roll the tape please?
Thank you.

18
00:02:59,279 --> 00:03:02,339
The core satellite is designed
like a TRMM Spacecraft.

19
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:08,018
It'll be launched in non-sun-sync
orbit at an inclination of 65-degrees

20
00:03:08,454 --> 00:03:10,854
and an altitude of 400 kms.

21
00:03:11,824 --> 00:03:15,487
The constellation satellites would be
pre-existing operational, experimental &

22
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:19,756
dedicated satellites,
with PMW radiometers.

23
00:03:21,201 --> 00:03:24,227
They would operate both in
non-sun-synch and synch orbits

24
00:03:24,437 --> 00:03:27,099
at an altitude of 600-900 kms.

25
00:03:37,784 --> 00:03:39,513
You are welcome to
throw any questions.

26
00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:44,851
What are the objectives of the Global
Precipitation Measurement programme?

27
00:03:49,028 --> 00:03:51,394
Last question.
- Is this budget justified?

28
00:03:52,432 --> 00:03:55,424
Globally, there is a danger of
water recession in the near future.

29
00:03:56,502 --> 00:04:00,700
It will not be unreal to imagine that
in the 21st century, cities like

30
00:04:01,441 --> 00:04:09,473
Beijing, Amman, New Delhi, Santiago,
Jakarta, Mexico City, Lima

31
00:04:09,983 --> 00:04:15,114
and many others, will drink up, use up
their surrounding waters and perish.

32
00:04:16,389 --> 00:04:22,521
Water is going to be rare. Is it not a
reason enough to justify any budget?

33
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:29,432
Are there any more questions?

34
00:04:31,037 --> 00:04:34,131
Thank you for being here.
- Thank you very much.

35
00:04:44,751 --> 00:04:47,083
I've never seen John Stockton
smile so much.

36
00:04:47,387 --> 00:04:48,479
He is really very happy with us.

37
00:04:49,155 --> 00:04:52,613
The press conference went off well.
And your presentation excellent!

38
00:04:53,593 --> 00:04:54,958
This is a quantum leap for us.

39
00:04:56,396 --> 00:05:00,992
Well, we can now let our hair down
now that Phase I is finally over.

40
00:05:07,106 --> 00:05:10,337
Hey, you've been very quiet.
What's the matter?

41
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:19,513
I want to get a cup of coffee.
Would you like some?

42
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:23,145
Make me a strong one.
- Sure

43
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,757
Two new messages,

44
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:32,521
Hi Mohan. This is Paul tried
calling you at work and your cell

45
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:34,290
you seem to be in a meeting,
call me back.

46
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:44,738
Good afternoon Mr. Bhargava, this is
Steven Carter from the BCIS...

47
00:05:45,311 --> 00:05:51,216
... your request for citizenship has been
accepted. Please call me on Monday. Bye.

48
00:05:59,325 --> 00:06:02,453
Congratulations! Your request for
citizenship has been accepted.

49
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:09,361
You seem lost.
- Not really.

50
00:06:11,304 --> 00:06:15,263
I get it. Work pressures are
stressing you out

51
00:06:15,641 --> 00:06:18,940
and then you have no other interests...
No pubbing, no partying!

52
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,612
Take my advice,
you should get married!

53
00:06:26,586 --> 00:06:28,679
You need a life partner.

54
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:32,490
Like they say - Happiness
only doubles when it is shared!

55
00:06:32,658 --> 00:06:34,353
It changed My life!

56
00:06:36,295 --> 00:06:38,058
No Vinod, that's not it.

57
00:06:40,199 --> 00:06:41,564
Then what is it?

58
00:06:46,506 --> 00:06:47,632
What's the matter?

59
00:06:49,175 --> 00:06:51,302
Today is the death anniversary
of my parents.

60
00:06:52,178 --> 00:06:53,873
Oh! I'm sorry.

61
00:06:56,816 --> 00:06:57,908
No, It's okay.

62
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:05,715
I still vividly remember that I was in my
last year of University in Pennsylvania

63
00:07:07,226 --> 00:07:08,989
... when I received the news
of their car accident!

64
00:07:11,697 --> 00:07:14,359
Now I understand why
you've been so low all day.

65
00:07:17,503 --> 00:07:18,731
You know Vinod...

66
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:22,474
There's something else,
which has been

67
00:07:22,975 --> 00:07:25,375
pricking my conscience
these last few months.

68
00:07:27,246 --> 00:07:31,683
Do you remember Kaveriamma?

69
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:36,755
Kaveriamma? Your old
maid servant, right?

70
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:40,854
Please don't call her a maidservant.
She was like a mother to me!

71
00:07:42,061 --> 00:07:46,998
I'm sorry. I had no idea.
What about her?

72
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:51,795
As you know,
I was the only child.

73
00:07:53,906 --> 00:07:59,503
My parents brought me up with a lot of
love, they provided me with everything.

74
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:06,113
But along with them, Kaveriamma too
had a special place in my life.

75
00:08:08,588 --> 00:08:10,055
My mother would
make my breakfast,

76
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:12,723
while Kaveriamma would feed me.

77
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:18,726
My parents tucked me into bed,
while Kaveriamma sang me a lullaby.

78
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:26,569
From the age of two to seventeen
she looked after me completely.

79
00:08:28,975 --> 00:08:34,208
You could say Kaveriamma was
like a second mother to me

80
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:40,885
So when was the last time
you met her?

81
00:08:44,457 --> 00:08:48,257
At my parent's funeral.

82
00:08:50,396 --> 00:08:53,559
I remember crying like a child
in Kaveriamma's arms.

83
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:57,665
It was a very tough time for me.

84
00:08:58,871 --> 00:09:02,398
Then I came back here and
began to find a footing in life.

85
00:09:03,509 --> 00:09:06,706
Kaveriamma would often write me letters,
and I would send her replies as well.

86
00:09:08,514 --> 00:09:15,545
But later, I got so completely immersed in
my work, that I just lost touch.

87
00:09:18,491 --> 00:09:21,153
All this is so out of the blue Mohan.

88
00:09:21,794 --> 00:09:24,695
why did you suddenly
think of her today?

89
00:09:25,364 --> 00:09:26,695
It's not sudden, Vinod.

90
00:09:28,701 --> 00:09:31,261
I've been thinking about her
since the past few months.

91
00:09:33,172 --> 00:09:35,402
I've been having recurring
nightmares of her being...

92
00:09:37,043 --> 00:09:39,534
... old, feeble, and helpless.

93
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:44,773
Vinod, I have blundered.

94
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:52,114
I now feel very guilty
that I have neglected her...

95
00:09:53,659 --> 00:09:56,127
... and haven't been able to
look after her.

96
00:09:57,763 --> 00:09:59,458
I had become selfish Vinod.

97
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:06,400
She is the only thread who can
string the memories of my parents.

98
00:10:18,017 --> 00:10:21,714
I was thinking of going to Delhi...
and bringing her here.

99
00:10:23,122 --> 00:10:25,386
Absolutely! Brilliant idea!

100
00:10:26,859 --> 00:10:28,292
But I don't think John will consent.

101
00:10:28,894 --> 00:10:32,125
There can't be a better time for you
to ask for a vacation than now,

102
00:10:33,232 --> 00:10:37,225
We are 28 weeks away from
the GPM launch. John won't refuse.

103
00:10:40,006 --> 00:10:42,702
You think so?
- Yeah sure.

104
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:46,570
Promise to bring him back an
elephant or something.

105
00:10:48,881 --> 00:10:50,075
Yeah sure!

106
00:11:05,097 --> 00:11:06,121
Thank you very much.

107
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:11,835
So its on the outmost importance
to get the time pressure on the

108
00:11:12,038 --> 00:11:13,096
stabilization unit.

109
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:15,773
Thank you very much gentlemen.

110
00:11:18,878 --> 00:11:20,573
Excuse me John.
- Sure, tell me.

111
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:24,983
I have a request for two weeks off.
Need to go to India, is it possible?

112
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:27,915
Is everything ok back home?

113
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,811
Oh yeah everything is allright.
Just a pending matter.

114
00:11:31,023 --> 00:11:32,251
When do you have to leave?

115
00:11:32,792 --> 00:11:34,259
Actually as soon as possible.

116
00:11:35,728 --> 00:11:37,389
28 weeks to launch?

117
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:40,263
You realize you have to delegate
some of this to others.

118
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,496
Oh yes yes I'll have a detailed
meeting with the team and

119
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,295
I'll be in constant touch
with Vinod from here.

120
00:11:46,839 --> 00:11:49,740
Alright then, have a good trip.

121
00:11:49,909 --> 00:11:51,171
Thank you very much John.

122
00:11:54,113 --> 00:11:57,947
Amazing... John agreed very quickly.
I should have asked for a vacation myself.

123
00:11:58,117 --> 00:12:00,813
Thank God you didn't. If you had,
he would have cancelled mine too.

124
00:12:51,937 --> 00:12:55,600
May I clear your tray please?
Can I get you anything else?

125
00:12:55,741 --> 00:12:56,969
No thank you.

126
00:13:27,673 --> 00:13:30,073
This is your Captain here.
Good morning everyone.

127
00:13:31,243 --> 00:13:32,767
We have now started our descent

128
00:13:33,045 --> 00:13:35,343
And in a short time we'll be landing

129
00:13:35,614 --> 00:13:37,809
at the Indira Gandhi
International Airport in Delhi.

130
00:13:39,718 --> 00:13:44,917
Hope you had a comfortable flight
Thank you for flying Air India.

131
00:14:29,401 --> 00:14:30,732
Your attention please.

132
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:36,840
Announcing the arrival of flight
Al-112 from New York

133
00:14:39,845 --> 00:14:41,312
Good to see you.
- Good to see you too.

134
00:14:41,614 --> 00:14:44,344
How was the flight?
- Connecting flight was delayed. Rest ok!

135
00:14:44,817 --> 00:14:47,786
Did you get anything for me?
- Yeah, everything's for you, kid!

136
00:14:50,422 --> 00:14:54,051
So Kaveriamma... is she still living
in an Old age Home?

137
00:14:55,694 --> 00:14:56,991
Did you speak with her?

138
00:14:57,563 --> 00:15:00,054
No, I want to surprise her!

139
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:03,902
She'll be so glad to see you.
I'm sure she'll have forgotten me.

140
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:05,294
Obviously!

141
00:15:28,694 --> 00:15:32,095
Excuse me.
- Yes? May I help you?

142
00:15:33,065 --> 00:15:34,794
I've come to meet Kaveriamma.

143
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,929
Kaveriamma?
- Yes.

144
00:15:38,037 --> 00:15:40,767
Kaveri oh yes! She doesn't
live with us any longer.

145
00:15:43,342 --> 00:15:46,334
Doesn't live here?
- She stayed with us for about a year...

146
00:15:46,545 --> 00:15:49,776
... till a woman came looking for her.
And then, Kaveri left with her.

147
00:15:52,351 --> 00:15:53,909
But where did she go?

148
00:15:54,186 --> 00:15:56,711
Just a minute,
I'll have to check the register.

149
00:16:03,629 --> 00:16:08,726
Bharati<i>ji</i>, this gentleman is
looking for Kaveri.

150
00:16:09,702 --> 00:16:11,169
Do you know where
is she now?

151
00:16:11,737 --> 00:16:14,069
Bharati<i>ji</i> used to share
the room with Kaveri.

152
00:16:14,740 --> 00:16:17,937
I remember her mentioning
a village before leaving.

153
00:16:18,844 --> 00:16:20,277
Now what was it... ?

154
00:16:21,747 --> 00:16:24,409
Charanpur.
- That's right, Charanpur.

155
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,349
Where is this Charanpur?
- Never heard of it.

156
00:16:30,689 --> 00:16:31,849
We'll find out.

157
00:16:34,460 --> 00:16:36,052
Kaveri was a good woman.

158
00:16:36,795 --> 00:16:38,854
We all miss her.

159
00:16:40,566 --> 00:16:41,760
Here's the address.

160
00:16:43,135 --> 00:16:44,102
Thank you!

161
00:16:47,773 --> 00:16:49,570
Kaveri is very fortunate.

162
00:16:50,609 --> 00:16:54,238
There was someone who came
for her then, and now once again.

163
00:16:55,247 --> 00:16:58,216
Otherwise who cares
for old ones like us?

164
00:17:01,887 --> 00:17:02,751
Come on.

165
00:17:10,896 --> 00:17:11,794
Excuse me.

166
00:17:12,598 --> 00:17:14,998
Here's the map.
You'll find Charanpur in here.

167
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:17,699
That'll be 150 rupees.
- That's ok. Don't pay me.

168
00:17:19,271 --> 00:17:22,104
Do me a favor. Watch the counter
for me while I nip to the bank.

169
00:17:22,307 --> 00:17:25,868
Get me a loan too!
- Sure, you'll manage the counter, right?

170
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:27,736
I'll just sit behind.

171
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:30,277
That's good.
- Come back soon.

172
00:17:39,992 --> 00:17:41,584
Excuse me you've no respect?

173
00:17:42,361 --> 00:17:43,521
What happened?

174
00:17:43,929 --> 00:17:47,763
You can see I am picking up books,
and still you're walking all over them.

175
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,433
I did not mean to.

176
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:53,295
Look, books are a source
of knowledge and culture...

177
00:17:53,472 --> 00:17:56,202
and if you don't know how to respect
them, you shouldn't be here.

178
00:17:56,608 --> 00:18:00,510
Well I'm sorry.
- Thanks.

179
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:36,107
I'm sorry, I was just
looking at this map.

180
00:18:39,918 --> 00:18:41,749
You want to buy these books?

181
00:18:42,588 --> 00:18:43,919
No! I want to sell them!!

182
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:48,651
Oh stupid question, I'm sorry.
- No I'm sorry.

183
00:18:48,861 --> 00:18:52,854
Actually I'm just a little irritated.
- No, I saw what happened.

184
00:18:53,565 --> 00:18:54,896
You dealt with the man right.

185
00:18:55,033 --> 00:18:57,501
Some people just don't have
the basic etiquette.

186
00:18:59,771 --> 00:19:03,639
Oh yeah... I'll do this for you.
Lots of books.

187
00:19:06,745 --> 00:19:08,838
I will need a...
- Over there.

188
00:19:09,214 --> 00:19:11,114
Yes, thank you.

189
00:19:11,950 --> 00:19:17,286
That's 13 books of Mathematics into 17...

190
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:23,587
... is equal to 221/- + 22 Language
books into 12 is equal to...

191
00:19:23,795 --> 00:19:24,989
Four-eighty five.

192
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:31,860
Four-eighty five!

193
00:19:33,272 --> 00:19:38,733
That's 8 Geography books into
19 is 152, plus 485 is...

194
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:40,611
Six-thirty Seven!

195
00:19:42,147 --> 00:19:47,380
Really 637? Thanks.

196
00:19:48,787 --> 00:19:56,023
And these 8 note books at 113
and the total is...

197
00:19:56,828 --> 00:19:58,022
Seven fifty.

198
00:19:58,664 --> 00:19:59,688
Must be right!

199
00:20:01,767 --> 00:20:06,830
750 it is.
Your... maths is pretty good!

200
00:20:12,544 --> 00:20:14,068
Actually, I should be
giving you a concession.

201
00:20:14,479 --> 00:20:16,572
You selected the books,
you did the totalling...

202
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:18,349
you should be in my chair!

203
00:20:19,084 --> 00:20:20,415
Then give me a concession?

204
00:20:21,787 --> 00:20:22,981
Sorry I can't!

205
00:20:24,489 --> 00:20:27,390
Actually my name is Mohan Bhargav.
I'm Rahul's friend...

206
00:20:28,727 --> 00:20:32,060
... he's the owner of this shop,
he's just gone to the bank...

207
00:20:32,931 --> 00:20:35,991
... he was broke you see...
needed to get some money

208
00:20:36,168 --> 00:20:37,499
I'm just filling in for him.

209
00:20:38,203 --> 00:20:39,170
Oh!

210
00:20:40,272 --> 00:20:42,706
I'll just pack this for you
I just need...

211
00:20:42,874 --> 00:20:43,841
Bags.

212
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:50,876
I have been looking
for Charanpur in this map

213
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:53,278
It's a small little village.

214
00:20:53,485 --> 00:20:55,953
Have you heard of it?

215
00:20:59,791 --> 00:21:01,258
Yes, I know where it is.

216
00:21:02,628 --> 00:21:07,088
Go down National Highway No. 6 for
110 kms till you reach Charoti.

217
00:21:08,533 --> 00:21:10,091
Take a left from there.

218
00:21:10,302 --> 00:21:13,271
Then keep going for 80 kms till
you reach Azamgarh.

219
00:21:13,972 --> 00:21:18,568
From there 20 kms on a dirt track,
you'll reach Charanpur.

220
00:21:19,344 --> 00:21:24,441
Wow! Your geography seems
pretty good as well!

221
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:29,985
Here you...

222
00:21:32,157 --> 00:21:33,624
Hello! Excuse me.

223
00:21:36,261 --> 00:21:38,695
Please look after the counter...

224
00:21:51,777 --> 00:21:54,143
What happened?
You sick of the job already?

225
00:21:54,279 --> 00:21:58,579
No, a girl came in, bought a lot of
books... but left without her change.

226
00:21:58,950 --> 00:22:00,076
Hey! Not bad!

227
00:22:00,419 --> 00:22:03,047
You made a profit for the company on the
very first day! You've got the job!

228
00:22:04,189 --> 00:22:05,156
She was amazing!

229
00:22:06,391 --> 00:22:07,722
She even gave me directions
to Charanpur!

230
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:09,358
Great, where is it?

231
00:22:10,562 --> 00:22:12,189
About 200 kms from here.

232
00:22:13,398 --> 00:22:16,526
Spare me Mohan. Don't expect me to
leave the store and drive you there.

233
00:22:16,735 --> 00:22:20,694
No worries!
I'll need a car though.

234
00:22:20,906 --> 00:22:25,206
Take mine.
- No, no. Could I get a caravan?

235
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:27,037
Caravan? What for?

236
00:22:27,913 --> 00:22:30,473
Don't know the conditions I'll have
to face in the village.

237
00:22:32,417 --> 00:22:34,385
Ok, ok Mr. NRI
<i>(Non-Resident Indian)</i>

238
00:22:34,753 --> 00:22:36,550
You'll have your caravan.
Don't worry.

239
00:22:39,791 --> 00:22:44,751
<i>(Old Hindi film song)</i>

